column7: Tips & Tricks from a Pro Sair
DPS is nice, but don't worry about gear/range at the start. Learn mechanics instead.
Learning boss hit animations is very useful - start with learning 1/1s at least
Always use homing beacon on each boss part you attack. Make sure you see the parrot animation above it.
Ice split + flame throw is a good macro for quick mobbing and fast mobility.
Another good macro is octopus + gaviota + battleship (can be used as a dismount macro if timed right, then rapid fire or re-mount after getting hit)
Use pet gear to max jump and speed - it helps the recoil shot + wings macro.
